 ('14', '14', 'en_us', 'The Burr', '<p>The Burr is Kent State University\'s first student magazine. Published once a semester, The Burr looks into current trends, issues and people in Kent and the surrounding communities. Each issue contains a compelling mix of original reporting, in depth issue coverage, profiles and personal essays. The web counterpoint TheBurr.com features online feature stories and multimedia as well as weekly blogs on topics such as relationships, fashion, health and entertainment. The Burr has been producing strong, award-winning journalism since 1986.</p>', NULL, 'theburrmagazine@gmail.com', '[]', 'Sammi', 'Ickes', 'Student Leader', NULL, '330-672-2947', 'The Burr is an independent, award-winning student magazine and was Kent State’s first student magazine ever. The magazine features a mix of original reporting, how-to articles, feature articles and personal essays. TheBurr.com is frequently updated with multimedia stories and blogs and has an archive of past issues.', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The Burr is Kent State’s first student-produced magazine made for those who have made a home in Kent.', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-02-27 15:21:05', '2017-05-11 18:34:23', '45cdefa8-367e-4d2d-9733-583b8f9829b4'),
 ('15', '15', 'en_us', 'Kent Stater', '<p>The Kent Stater is an award-winning student-run newspaper. Reaching more than 9,500 people per issue, the Stater keeps the community up-to-date with campus, local and national news, sports and features. The Stater publishes on Monday, Wednesday and Thursday and has a circulation of 6,000 per day. During the summer months, The Kent Stater runs special print issues and the annual Orientation issue to welcome back students. The Kent Stater publishes online with media partner, TV2, at KentWired.com\n      </p>', NULL, 'kentwired@gmail.com', '[]', 'Jimmy', 'Miller', 'Student Leader', NULL, '330-672-2586', 'The Kent Stater is the award-winning, student-run newspaper at Kent State University. Reaching more than 15,000 people per issue, the Stater keeps the community up-to-date with campus, local and national news, sports and features. The Stater publishes on Monday, Wednesday and Thursday and has a circulation of 6,750 per day. During the summer months, The Kent Stater runs special print issues and also runs the annual Orientation issue to welcome new and returning students.', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The Kent Stater is the award-winning, student-run newspaper at Kent State University. ', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-02-27 15:21:14', '2017-05-11 18:35:57', '7e622988-7d52-4011-872c-1c063f8dcc6e'),
 ('19', '19', 'en_us', 'Black Squirrel Radio', '<p>Black Squirrel Radio is a student-run radio station committed to providing innovative media content inspired by the community of Kent, Ohio, dedicated to professionalism, integrity, creativity and diversity. With 56 different student-hosted shows airing from 10am to 2am everyday, we are committed to providing professional industry experience while continuing to be a platform for experimental programming. Through alternative media content, we aim to grow our audience by becoming the destination for students and alumni to remember what was and experience what is college life in Kent, Ohio.</p>', NULL, 'lgerbig@kent.edu', '[]', 'Layne', 'Gerbig', 'Student Leader', NULL, '', 'Black Squirrel Radio (BSR) is a student-run radio station that has 10,000 loyal monthly listeners. BSR features a large selection of urban, rock and local music with numerous local bands and entertainers coming for in-studio performances and interviews. BSR is available at www.blacksquirrelradio.com, iTunes radio under College Stations, the TuneIn app and channels 2-4 and 2-6 though on-campus television.', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Black Squirrel Radio (BSR) is the student-run radio station on Kent State’s campus and provides innovative media content inspired by the community of Kent, Ohio.', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-03-02 19:46:01', '2017-05-28 23:21:43', 'b9058ae3-0353-4198-93c6-ca8357c03eb1'),
 ('20', '20', 'en_us', 'TV2', '<p>TV2 is Kent State\'s award winning television station that strives to be Truly Portage County. From local news and sports to entertainment buzz and important social issues surrounding the region, TV2 covers the Kent State and Portage County area like no other television station can, while educating and preparing students for the future.</p>', NULL, 'lkober@kent.edu', '[]', 'Leisel', 'Kober', 'Student Leader', NULL, '330-672-2584', 'TV2 is the award-winning, student-run television station of Kent State University. TV2 is also Portage County’s only local television station and the best source for local news and original television content. TV2 reaches more than 26,000 homes throughout Portage County on Spectrum (formerly Time Warner Cable) channel 16 and more than 7,500 Kent State students living on-campus on channel 2-2. TV2 is also live streamed on KentWired.com/TV2. With 10 different TV shows, TV2 covers everything from breaking news, local news, weather, sports, entertainment and humor.', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'TV2 is Kent State\'s award winning television station that strives to be Truly Portage County.', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-03-02 19:46:26', '2017-05-31 19:59:52', 'a23b03af-0e18-4a7b-8901-95644568668e'),
 ('21', '21', 'en_us', 'Fusion Magazine', '<p>Fusion is Kent State University\'s LGBTQ magazine. We publish news, entertainment, opinions and interviews for and about the LGBTQ community. Each spring, we release a print issue and we regularly update our website year-round. </p>\n<p>Our mission is to promote equality, education and community through journalism. When Fusion was founded, in 2003, marriage equality was not yet legal anywhere in the United States and laws against consensual sex between gay men were overturned that year. LGBTQ rights have significantly advanced since trans women, drag queens and street kids fought back against police violence in 1959. But the community, particularly trans people and people of color, still face substantial adversity. Journalism and storytelling helps humanize the community and its struggle. By publicizing their perspectives and experiences, Fusion helps demonstrate why LGBTQ people need an equal place in society.</p>', NULL, 'meckhous@kent.edu', '[]', 'MJ', 'Eckhouse', 'Student Leader', NULL, '', 'Fusion is Kent State\'s lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender and queer/questioning student advocacy and entertainment magazine. Fusion strives to promote equality and community in northeast Ohio and beyond through journalism and they have been recognized by the Society of Professional Journalists for excellence. Fusion is the only student magazine focusing on LGBTQ issues in the region.', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Fusion is Kent State\'s lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender and queer/questioning student advocacy and entertainment magazine.', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-03-02 19:46:47', '2017-05-11 03:27:21', '7588d518-0261-46ab-a865-1600d104616c'),
 ('22', '22', 'en_us', 'Uhuru', '<p>Uhuru is an award-winning magazine that aims to promote innovation, creativity, and culture through the voice of marginalized students on the Kent State University campus. Having a history of pan-African teachings and values, Uhuru magazine focuses on the plight of all students around the globe.\n  </p>\n<p>Uhuru, which is Kiswahili for ‘freedom,’ serves as a platform for student creation and expression in art, writing, photography and graphic design, while discussing racial, social and/or political ignorance.\n      </p>', NULL, 'uhurumag1@gmail.com', '[]', 'Sierra', 'Allen', 'Student Leader', NULL, '', 'Uhuru is an award-winning magazine that promotes innovation, creativity and culture through the voice of marginalized students. A derivative of Black Unites Students, Uhuru is focused on the unification of the African-American population but serves as a safe haven for others by reflecting all people of color at Kent State. Uhuru is Kent State\'s only minority news outlet and serves as a platform for student creation and expression in art, writing, photography and graphic design while addressing social issues.', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Uhuru is the magazine that promotes innovation, creativity and culture through the voice of marginalized students at Kent State.', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-03-02 19:46:53', '2017-05-11 18:32:04', 'b1238632-d5b9-44ea-a4f5-8584bb4f074e'),
 ('23', '23', 'en_us', 'KentWired', '<p>KentWired.com is the hub of all Kent State Student Media. Featuring top news, entertainment, community and campus news, sports and video, KentWired is the place to turn to for everything Kent. The site also features  classifieds, daily podcasts, newscasts and live streams to TV2 and Black Squirrel Radio. KentWired is also the key source to news over the summer months.</p>', NULL, 'kentwired@gmail.com', '[]', '', '', '', NULL, '330-672-2586', 'KentWired.com is a news organization hosting content created by the collaborative effort of students working in student media at Kent State University. KentWired is the independent news website for the Kent Stater and TV2 and is the year round news source for everything Kent. KentWired has top news, entertainment, sports, and community and campus news. It also features classifieds and live streams for TV2 and Black Squirrel Radio. ', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'KentWired.com is a news organization that holds content created by students working in student media at Kent State University. ', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-03-02 19:48:46', '2017-05-11 18:30:51', 'ecc0b93e-3f1e-4938-9f03-c3892be4e7ac'),
 ('24', '24', 'en_us', 'Luna Negra', '<p>Luna Negra, though sometimes under different names, has been around since 1956. It began under the English department, where it found its footing within the campus’s cultural atmosphere. Since then, the publication has been a staple of the university, witnessing the path Kent State has taken through the decades. We have published works describing the culture of collegiate 1950s, the Kent State shootings, and 9/11; the literary pieces published by Luna Negra, written by the students themselves, have chronicled every major cultural and historical event of America. Since its inception, and still to today, Luna Negra is run by students and filled with student content. We strive to foster creative activity across campus and seek to be the keeper and encourager of the student body’s creative spirit.</p>', NULL, 'lunanegramag@gmail.com', '[]', 'Sam', 'Hersh', 'Student Leader', NULL, '', 'Luna Negra is Kent State’s literary student publication and they publish a blend of poetry, prose, photography and illustration. For over 50 years, they have published submissions from current students and community members. Their magazine is published every spring and they produce additional content on LunaNegraMag.com.', NULL, NULL, 'fsfsdfdsfds', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Luna Negra is Kent State’s literary student magazine that publishes a blend of poetry, prose, photography and illustration. ', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-03-02 19:49:24', '2017-06-01 18:46:27', '64fa8053-5481-4595-9f99-d2f2720dbed5'),
 ('25', '25', 'en_us', 'KSU Independent Films', '<p>Kent State University Independent Films (KSUIF) is an organization fueled by students’ passion for film. In 2008, professors Traci E. Williams and David Smeltzer collaborated to create this wonderful program, which is designed to give students real-world film experience. Today, nearly 500 people are currently involved in the organization.</p>', NULL, 'kentstatefilms@gmail.com', '[]', 'Erica', 'Collins', 'Student Leader', NULL, '330-672-8198', 'Kent State University Independent Films (KSUIF) is a student-run production company that teaches, inspires and prepares filmmakers for the real-world industry. KSUIF produces a wide variety of content including webseries, short films, award-winning music videos, documentaries, TV shows and feature films. KSUIF is one of three organizations in the country that allows students to create full-length feature films.', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Kent State University Independent Films (KSUIF) is a student-run production company that teaches, inspires and prepares filmmakers for the real-world industry. ', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-03-02 19:49:47', '2017-05-11 18:30:18', 'd408f63f-0d5c-42e8-84c9-70b90293d6dd'),
